page.title: 01Prestwood - Brief outline
page.content: The area we live in is mostly agricultural and wooded. Prestwood village has grown much larger since World War II. Most houses in our village were built since 1950, both council and private types. Private houses cost from 40,000 pounds upwards. Building continues but mostly to the S.E. of our grid. Most people living here work outside of this area. In 1881 there were less than 800 people in Prestwood, most employed in agriculture. Much of our text is about children in Prestwood. Our school is 200 metres outside of the most S.E. Km. Square of our grid. We decided we would use Domesday to find out some facts about ourselves. The beautiful countryside in our area is shown in our photographs. We do have easy access to London, and High Wycombe is our nearest town.
